Windows Registry Editor Version 5.00
; Disables Hypervisor-Enforced Code Integrity (HVCI) to improve system performance.
; This key disables the feature that enforces code integrity at the hypervisor level, which can prevent some unsigned drivers from running.
; Disabling it may improve system performance but reduces system security.

[HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\DeviceGuard\Scenarios\HypervisorEnforcedCodeIntegrity]
"Enabled"=dword:00000000